begin
reserve X for BCI-algebra;
reserve I for (Ideal of X);
theorem
(I is (associative-ideal of X) implies (for x being (Element of X) holds ( x \ ( ( 0. X ) \ x ) ) in I))
proof
assume A1: I is (associative-ideal of X);
let x being (Element of X);
( x \ x ) = ( 0. X ) by BCIALG_1:def 5;
then A2: ( ( x \ ( 0. X ) ) \ x ) = ( 0. X ) by BCIALG_1:2;
( 0. X ) in I by A1,CKB18:def 1;
hence thesis by A1,A2,CKB20:1;
end;
